Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.68,0:00:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain rises on a mysterious new era...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.56,0:00:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Monday 7:00 reasoning show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.77,0:00:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the puzzling case of the "Fuurinkazan."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan and Heiji bring it to its final conclusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.82,0:00:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.53,0:00:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.36,0:00:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.34,0:01:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The feuding Torada and Tatsuo families\Nare involved in a serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.38,0:02:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crimes are being patterned\Nafter Takeda Shingen's "Fuurinkazan."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.85,0:02:05.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is the culprit so obsessed with Shingen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's the connection with the falling\Ndeath of Officer Kai Kuroto six years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.69,0:02:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the mystery deepens, eventually there's a new victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.62,0:02:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been burnt black from top to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.21,0:02:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But looking at the shape, there's no doubt it was Torada Shigetsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.08,0:02:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tatsuo family must have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.58,0:02:37.97,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Torada Naonobu (61)\NHead of the Torada Family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of foolish talk is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, where\Ndid that fishing pole go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.30,0:02:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fishing pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It was in a case, but I think it was probably a fishing pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.14,0:02:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, a fishing pole? Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.81,0:02:54.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} touched the train's aerial electrical wiring\Nwith this long fishing pole and was electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.94,0:02:54.27,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)} Torada Yui (29)\NYoshirou's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.73,0:02:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did you find that pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.07,0:02:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right there in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case for the pole had been\Ndropped over by the railroad crossing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.74,0:03:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he must have taken it out there, and\Nafter he was hit by the electrical shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.66,0:03:10.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figure it must have been struck by the train and hurled there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.96,0:03:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next to the case, someone has placed the corpse of a centipede.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.29,0:03:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is another serial murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.84,0:03:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torada Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was killed by a tornado, is "wind".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was buried in the\Nground and beaten to death, is "mountain".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was hanged in the woods, is "forest".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.15,0:03:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Torada Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who received an electrical\Nshock and was burned completely black, is "fire".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.28,0:03:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Fuurinkazan" has been successfully completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.24,0:03:44.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Akira (32)\NTamefumi's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:46.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But, why did my wife and my friends\Nhave to be killed in this horrible way?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.32,0:03:50.25,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Yamato Kansuke (35)\NNagano Prefectural\NPolice Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.62,0:03:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamato, there's\Na strange notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.79,0:03:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This seems to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A record of their progress in searching for the buried gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:04:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, could that possibly be the memo pad\Nthat Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but this was also used as a shared diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In summary, what's written in the diary says...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That six years ago they accidentally caused a certain person's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They fought with the idea of going to the police\Nor not, but in the end, they didn't say anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they've remained silent ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.90,0:04:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Akira, they did it for your sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second. Six years ago? That means the dead person was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:33.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Kai Kuroto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that you would win at the preliminary contest\Nand be chosen as the horseback archery bowman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.51,0:04:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wanted to cause Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to be injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.47,0:04:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They used fireworks to frighten Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s horse\Nwhile he was practicing, hoping he'd be thrown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the horse became more frightened\Nthat they thought, and it started running.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when they followed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says they found that Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, along\Nwith his horse, had fallen off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.81,0:04:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the handwriting, I'd say four\Npeople were writing in this shared diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.15,0:05:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd dare say it's those who've recently died:\NYoshirou and Shigetsugu from the Torada family...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kouji and Ayaka from the Tatsuo family, those four people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would that notebook be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to send it to hell, and keep all of this hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu made a show of looking for this note-\Nbook, but in truth he had it concealed on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.13,0:05:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He kept hold of it as he burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.17,0:05:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that was his way of apologizing to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're not saying, this series of murders was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.47,0:05:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.72,0:05:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After consigning his partners in the crime six years ago to oblivion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.19,0:05:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As his last act, he killed himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.52,0:05:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to bury the truth in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torada Shigetsugu was the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he attempted to destroy this notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.49,0:05:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was so Tatsuo Akira would never know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.20,0:05:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, unfortunately for him, since it got hurled\Naway without being burned, it remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.12,0:05:58.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Still, if it was done in some part for Akira's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:06:01.63,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)} Tatsuo Tamefumi (56)\NHead of the Tatsuo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:06:01.63,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)} Tatsuo Shigeyo (78)\NTamefumi's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.08,0:06:01.63,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that, in the other world, he'll acknowledge him for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, this case is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this situation, I'd like to tell you all to\Nreturn peacefully to your homes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.31,0:06:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To complete my checking on this case, I need to\Nsearch your houses, so wait here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, did Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} actually find that notebook?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I didn't see him find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.91,0:06:32.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stopped searching and\Nstarted reading his cellphone e-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.87,0:06:34.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe he did find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.91,0:06:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just when we were about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.92,0:06:44.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it? Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.80,0:06:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rock with a string attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.14,0:06:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there was a string attached to that notebook too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bah, what does it matter? The case is already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} burned, that was "fire", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.78,0:07:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lightning? Does that mean it's going to rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lightning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.91,0:07:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it "lightning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.96,0:07:23.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is annoying, to think we're being made\Nto wait here in the middle of the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:26.38,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)} Torada Tatsue (58)\NNaonobu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.29,0:07:27.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, it was raining on the day my\Nhusband and the others killed Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband started having a lot of nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would mutter, "The sound... the flash..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He meant the lightning, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.93,0:07:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it was sunny that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.56,0:07:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.85,0:07:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My poor Shigetsugu will get rained on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Heiji, can't you do something about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.36,0:07:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those guys went off on their own again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.11,0:07:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here below the place where Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hanged...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.91,0:07:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no one else's footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.04,0:07:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are just the footprints and the marks of his cane that\Ndetective Yamato made when he brought the body down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When could the culprit have hanged Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disappeared from the restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both us and the members of the Torada family were there together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the people from the Tatsuo family were\Nbeing driven over by Tamefumi in his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.68,0:08:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.52,0:08:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's the police detective we met earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:34.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it looks like it's going to rain, Inspector\NYamato told us to come cover the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.16,0:08:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Whose coat is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this earlier, caught in a tree branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:41.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, that coat...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.79,0:08:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. The inspector asked me the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.88,0:08:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.21,0:08:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, please keep out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.55,0:08:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since the inspector came back, he's kept us\Nworking hard without even letting us have a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.05,0:08:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Came back"? Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.51,0:09:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went up into the mountains to find a man who had\Nskipped on his parole and got caught in an avalanche.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man was someone Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arrested for stealing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he'd vanished six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamato thought he might be\Nconnected to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s accidental death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, the inspector's left eye and left leg were injured...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he was unconscious the whole time that he was in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.25,0:09:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did that man have any connection to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.83,0:09:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it turned out they were unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But fate sure is cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who was his junior officer before he left, Uehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next time they met, she was the wife of a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.26,0:09:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though Uehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said they had to be absolutely\Nsure about what really happened when Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.74,0:09:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And despite both she and the inspector being so enthusiastic about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.16,0:09:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She suddenly quit her job as a detective and got married.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.77,0:09:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that those two became police detectives\Nin the first place because they admired Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.24,0:09:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so, then when she found Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nbody six years ago, she was a police detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.53,0:10:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since she was still new, it was a terrible\Nexperience for her and she cried over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of crying, there's one thing that's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.58,0:10:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Even though she must have\Nwiped away some tears before she died...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no other trace of her having cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know she wiped tears away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eye shadow in her left eye had been rubbed,\Nand some of it was still on her right index finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that make you think she wiped tears away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What color was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What color?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just common blue eye shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, lead your dark bay back to the Torada house right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:43.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.16,0:10:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears that this war...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.09,0:11:02.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Torada House
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.18,0:11:02.93,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What? The police are coming to search the house again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Inspector Yamato along with some of his junior officers will be coming tomorrow and staying over while they investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.60,0:11:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, they'll be searching the Tatsuo\Nhouse in the same way starting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long will they be staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be three or four days, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three or four days?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember right, the festival is three days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.62,0:11:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll have started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.95,0:11:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The festival, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.41,0:11:29.66,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo House
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.08,0:11:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouji.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.63,0:11:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.67,0:11:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you do that to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} just to help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.31,0:11:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you, just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.85,0:11:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torada Yui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.86,0:11:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? So you knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:11:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I'd be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.73,0:11:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.74,0:12:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because of what you said to yourself\Nwhen Shigetsugu died: "lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true that Shigetsugu san's body was\Nburned, the cause of his death was electrocution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.20,0:12:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wasn't "fire", it was the "lightning"\Nfrom "Move like the lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.33,0:12:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. There's more to the "Fuurinkazan"\Nstrategy that Sun Tzu advocated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Move like the lightning" that you just mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as impenetrable as a shadow."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "lightning" comes from "When you appear,\Nappear unexpectedly like the lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.56,0:12:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shadow" is from "When you hide, hide as still as a shadow."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.28,0:12:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the same way with Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} beneath the cliff where the sun didn't reach throughout the day, his breath growing still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.24,0:12:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To those four who caused Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death six years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His blood soaked undershirt must have looked deep red.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.08,0:12:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like the calvary troops wore in Takeda's "Akazonae".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.42,0:13:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why this was all patterned after Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was to flush out those four who caused Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.01,0:13:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as expected, Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} reacted to it almost instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} weren't that interested in Shingen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they didn't respond to the corpses of the centipedes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, it was with all that uproar that\Noccurred over the Suwa-style helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.19,0:13:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was finally smoked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.44,0:13:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then Ayaka was forced to revealed Shigetsugu's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you come to deal with me just like you did those four!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To wipe out Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}'s rival!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.83,0:13:34.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deal with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.33,0:13:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.96,0:13:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the person who's behind these serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From that person there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.30,0:13:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should have expected it from a former policewoman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.93,0:13:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you figure it out, I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.10,0:13:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the blue eye shadow on Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:14:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ao" (blue) from "aokage" (dark bay), meaning a black horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.81,0:14:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person riding a black horse at the time, which was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.28,0:14:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a clever little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.32,0:14:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you forced Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name\Nout of Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and dealt with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.33,0:14:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the child of my husband's former wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.29,0:14:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't related to me by blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why, Tatsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.34,0:14:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because she's the one who really killed Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.67,0:14:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mentioned it earlier, that my husband would say, "The\Nsound, the flash..." while he was having nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.55,0:14:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what lead me to realize there was another\Nperson at the crime scene six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.06,0:14:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it was you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wanted him injured as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.65,0:14:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I fired one shot from this gun at his horse's legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he plunged head over heels off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wouldn't you know, some people\Ncame and started making a big fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.79,0:14:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if they were the ones who caused his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.37,0:14:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That just made me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have been best if they continued\Nto think that and kept quiet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later on, he started talking about going to tell the police\Nabout the gunshot he'd heard and the flash he'd seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then the gods punished Yoshirou by sending him that tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you left my severely injured husband there to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leaving the centipede corpse you had already prepared there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.19,0:15:26.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, by that time, I'd already hit upon the idea of\Npatterning everything after the "Fuu-rin-ka-zan-in-rai".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.73,0:15:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that means one of your targets right from the start was Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the final one—\h"fire."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.62,0:15:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you've become a hindrance to the gambling\Nthat we sponsor, you'll be burned to a crisp.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.54,0:15:45.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll cook you with these flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.13,0:15:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gambling?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.63,0:15:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They gamble on the festival horseback archery demonstration,\Nbetting how many of the ten shots will be missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never missed a single one...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.05,0:15:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until you shifted one of the targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.22,0:16:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no point in gambling if he never misses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.35,0:16:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since you've hit them all for five years\Nstraight as well, you'll need to die too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The story will be that you took revenge for\Nyour Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}, whom you loved dearly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.82,0:16:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then to atone for those crimes, you took your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.20,0:16:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But considering the current circumstances...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having this stupid woman who, to solve the mystery of Officer Kai's death, went so far as to marry Yoshirou, a man she didn't love...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.25,0:16:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might look better if we change our story to\None where she kills you out of resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, will you tell this stupid woman something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.63,0:16:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why were there no marks beneath the place\Nwhere Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hanged on the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.22,0:16:40.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why waste words on someone about to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.81,0:16:47.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back then, you put Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on your horse, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used a rope you had already attached to the branch beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allowing you to hook it to her neck from the other side of the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you rode your horse up behind the tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So no one would know when the hoof marks had gotten there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.33,0:17:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here for two hours before you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the reason no one noticed\Nthat Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was on your horse was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.93,0:17:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had put a black coat on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Ayaka san was secluded in the restroom, you called\Nher by cellphone and secretly lured her out to the stables.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others left on the horses...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You placed her, with that black coat on her,\Nonto your black horse and went into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.90,0:17:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.82,0:17:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as quiet as the forest."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here, holding my breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.16,0:17:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it looks like an earlier visitor got here before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An earlier visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.54,0:17:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you know your target...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.92,0:17:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be cool and level...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit yourself down and observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:18:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be immovable like the mountain."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.06,0:18:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You planned this, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.69,0:18:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, with the police sticking around here until\Nthe festival, tonight was your only chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.65,0:18:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, compared to your plan of swiping that note-\Nbook, hanging it from the electric train wires...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And thereby electrocuting Shigetsugu, my plan was no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way you used a string to tie the notebook to a rock...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Made it simple to throw up and catch it on the aerial train wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} learned where it was from an e-mail you sent...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when he used the pole to get it, he was electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if you want to start a fire, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.72,0:18:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already called the fire department\Nand have them waiting on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.74,0:18:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'm striking with the blunt side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.50,0:19:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.29,0:19:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.17,0:19:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saved the best for yourself again, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An thus, the final murder was prevented before it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the war that had lasted for six years...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was over at last, with the enemy\Ngeneral sporting a bruise on her left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You fought a battle with the culprit and her gang last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.03,0:19:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you invite us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after all the support we've given you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.45,0:19:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiots, how could I get you involved in such a dangerous situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.58,0:19:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, please come in for a formal interview later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:19:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to come to the police as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.13,0:20:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.73,0:20:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because I thought you were dead, Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.98,0:20:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought I had to do something...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.53,0:20:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I married Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.99,0:20:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, when I say it like that, it makes me feel sorry for my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.45,0:20:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, didn't I just say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Come to the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.00,0:20:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you free yourself from your obligations,\Nand when you're ready —\hcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.30,0:20:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chief detective has been waiting too —\Nto taste that awful coffee you make again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, somehow those two...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.27,0:20:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are getting along!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what did those two say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were standing next to them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said, "Be as swift as the wind" or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strategy of love!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fuurinkazan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.29,0:22:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.95,0:22:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.83,0:22:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, just c'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.29,0:22:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.96,0:22:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.42,0:22:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hello, Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.01,0:22:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ran. What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.01,0:22:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.68,0:22:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today! Today's when I'm going to tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.81,0:22:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't we talk later?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.06,0:22:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! It's no good if we don't talk now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.73,0:23:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.94,0:23:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. I gotta go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.36,0:23:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Don't try and run away, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.90,0:23:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Attack as fiercely as the fire."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.00,0:23:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as quiet as the forest."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.63,0:23:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. It might be better to talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.88,0:23:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we leave it there for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.55,0:23:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.35,0:23:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.85,0:23:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think they're getting irritable because they're hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.73,0:23:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be immovable like the mountain."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.98,0:24:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.77,0:24:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,FOX\N(kitsune)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.15,0:24:26.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The setting next time is Yamaguchi Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.56,0:24:27.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Will I be going to?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.23,0:24:28.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You're not needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.07,0:24:29.78,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The broadcast is on Dec 1st.
